      <section eId="sec_SRULE-5-5">
        <num>SRULE 5.5</num>
        <heading>Section </heading>
        <subsection eId="SRULE-5-5__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>A quorum call to ascertain whether or not a quorum is present shall be in order at any time except when a member has the floor.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="SRULE-5-5__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>When a member of the Senate requests a quorum call, the Â President shall direct the Secretary to open the voting machine for a roll call. If a majority of the Senators answer the roll call, a quorum shall be deemed to be present. The same roll call procedure, to determine the presence of a quorum, shall be followed as the first order of business in the Morning Hour.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=180521</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
